and Pastry Arts, Bartending, Catering and Restaurant Management... View All Funeral Related Services Funeral Related Services Funeral Director, Mortuary Science... View All The fields of culinary arts and personal services include preparing food and providing beauty services. Read on to learn more about academic paths and career options in these fields. Inside Culinary Arts and Personal Services Culinary arts and personal services is a diverse field that can lead to a wide variety of career opportunities, depending on the field you choose to study and the level of study you attain. Most careers in the industry require that you gain professional experience prior to graduation. Some careers require that you earn licensure. Study.com has all the resources you need to learn about your occupational goals, what to expect and the training requirements. Education Information Aspiring chefs and other culinary professionals may earn associate, bachelor's or master's degrees in general culinary arts, or they can earn degrees targeted towards pastry arts or cake decorating. Those interested in this field can learn to prepare hot and cold meals, desserts, cakes and methods for presenting them in an aesthetically pleasing manner. Culinary Arts Associate Degree Culinary Arts Bachelor's Degree Culinary Arts Programs Students interested in personal service may learn how to dye and style hair, paint nails, provide skin care treatment and work with makeup. Full-time programs in cosmetology usually last 9-24 months, but training to be a manicurist, pedicurist, skin care specialist or electrologist can take less time. Certificate, diploma and associate degree programs are commonly available in the field of cosmetology. Here are a couple of links to Study.com articles with more details about training options. Cosmetology Courses Cosmetology Associate Degree Nail Technician Programs Distance Learning Options Although the majority of these programs have some hands-on requirements enabling you to gain experience cooking, cutting hair or applying makeup, some distance learning options are available. The following pages can provide you with information about what it entails. Online Cosmetology Courses Online Culinary Certificate Online Associate Degree in Culinary Arts Online Bachelor's Degree in Culinary Arts Management Licensure and Certification Information In careers where you'll be working on people's skin, hair and nails, you must earn certification and licensure. All 50 states have licensure or certification requirements for certain personal services careers. The U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) reports that public and private vocational schools often offer courses that can prepare students to receive certification in cosmetology and other personal appearance positions (www.bls.gov). Review the links below for more details. Cosmetology Licensure Cosmetology Instructor Certification Skin Care Specialist Certification Career Options Degree programs in culinary arts and personal services can lead to countless career opportunities. The following pages are a small selection illustrating your options and their educational requirements. Cosmetologist Makeup Artist Chef Pastry Artist Personal Chef Employment Outlook and Salary Information The occupational growth and change in demand for these positions varies greatly. For instance, the BLS stated that the demand for chefs and head cooks was expected to grow by only five percent from 2012-2022 and by two percent for food service managers. Individuals in cosmetology, including barbers, hairstylists and skincare specialists, could expect to see 13% growth over the same time period, which is about average compared to all other career fields. As of May 2013, the median annual salary for chefs and head cooks was $42,490, while food service managers made median salaries of $48,080. Barbers made median annual salaries of $25,010, manicurists made $19,340, skin care specialists made $28,940 and cosmetologists made $23,140. Read more Culinary Arts and Personal Services Related Articles RelatedRelated Articles Recently UpdatedRecent Articles PopularPopular Articles Top Schools for Culinary Arts and Culinary Services Find information about culinary arts and services programs, through which aspiring chefs can learn how to create menus, prepare a variety... Career Information for a Degree in Culinary Arts or Culinary Services Degrees in culinary arts or culinary services typically cover food service management, baking and pastry arts, culinary math, nutrition,... Culinary Arts Certificate Program Information Students interested in working in a professional kitchen may want to consider enrolling in a Culinary Arts Certificate program. These... Culinary Arts School in Ohio California Culinary Arts Culinary Arts Degrees in Arizona Culinary Arts Schools in Houston Culinary Arts School in Jacksonville Culinary Classes: Top Schools with Culinary Arts Programs - Seattle, WA Top School with a Culinary Arts Program in Charleston, SC Bachelor of Science in Information Technology: Online Degree Research online information technology courses and programs. Find out what you can learn in these courses and what you'll need in order to... Doctor of Divinity: Degree Program Information A Doctor of Divinity is an honorary degree. The title is bestowed to individuals who have devoted their lives to theological pursuits or... Do You Need a Bachelors Degree To Be a Wedding Coordinator? Career Information for a Degree in English Language and Literature Behavior Analyst: Job Description and Education Requirements Online PhD Programs in Engineering: Degree Overviews Adult School Programs for Becoming a Media Reporter Training Programs in Riverside Riverside, CA, residents have several options for vocational training programs available throughout the metropolitan region. Continue... Be a Rail Transportation Worker Options and Requirements Research the requirements to become a rail transportation wo